DESCRIPTION:Join us on Wednesday\, April 1st from 4–7 PM at Whispering Vine South Creek for a tasting that explores the bold\, expressive character of Argentina’s top wine regions. From high-altitude Cabernet Sauvignon to rich\, polished Malbec\, this lineup showcases the intensity\, structure\, and elegance that define Argentina’s modern winemaking.\nTasting Fee: $25 (Buy a bottle from the tasting and your fee is refunded)\nFeatured Wines:\n- Viña Cobos Bramare Luján de Cuyo Malbec 2023 – 93 pts Vinous – Juicy and plush with black fruit\, delicate cedar\, youthful energy\, and a polished finish.\n- Zolo Reserva Cabernet Sauvignon 2021 – 91 pts James Suckling\, 91 pts Vinous – Rich and generous with cassis\, sweet tobacco\, clove\, black tea\, and lightly chewy tannins.\n- Tapiz Black Tears Malbec – 96 pts James Suckling\, 92 pts Wine Spectator – Powerful and concentrated with blackberry\, blueberry\, dark chocolate\, mocha\, and a long\, luxurious finish.\n- Zaha Cabernet Sauvignon 2018 – 91 pts Wine Spectator\, Top 100 #73 – Bold and structured with blackberry\, cassis\, dark chocolate\, and polished tannins shaped by Andes-grown fruit.\nDiscover the depth and intensity of Argentina’s finest reds—buy a bottle and your tasting is free.
LOCATION:85 Foothill Rd Ste 1 Reno\, NV 89511
SUMMARY:Argentina Wines Tasting
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR